==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Latin]] [[impugnare]], from [[in-]] + [[pugnare]] ‘to fight’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-impugn.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*{{IPA|/ɪm'pju:n/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|impugn|impugns|impugned|impugning}}
# ''(transitive, obsolete)'' To [[assault]], [[attack]].
# ''(transitive)'' To verbally [[assault]], especially to argue against an opinion, motive, or action; to question the truth or validity of.

==== Synonyms ====
(''question the validity of''): [[call in question]], [[challenge]], [[contest]], [[contradict]], [[deny]], [[disavow]], [[dispute]], [[negate]]

==== Antonyms ====
(''question the validity of''): [[authenticate]], [[endorse]], [[support]]

